We shot this video early on in 2022 and I can see the pain and tiredness in my eyes.
There’s clearly some twitches of self doubt and uncertainty going on in my head. I can see it. I find the audio choice very fitting as my progression in loving myself has increased significantly since this time last year. I think this is a beautiful time capsule of vulnerability, insecurity, and my wavering confidence at the time. 

Everything is about love and I hope everyone can be patient enough to find it within themselves first. 🖤

This is a passion project I began creating while I was in rehab this past March and it isn’t something that’s easy to share. I hope no one laughs or makes fun of me. I consider it a sequel to another visual project I collaborated on with @yvestruong, which I made last year that discussed the double edged sword of beauty, consumerism, and the facade of perfectionism that many of us display to the world on the internet. I’ve always felt like I needed to highlight my struggles with substance abuse and sexual assaults on here, which for me seem to go hand in hand. The first time that I ever had a sexual experience I was 15 and under the influence, while a grown man coerced me into doing things I wasn’t comfortable with. I felt shameful and embarrassed. And instead of getting the correct care or having a conversation after, I bottled it up. I started a vicious cycle of drinking to numb my pain and inviting in new traumas through my drinking. It’s been a constant battle for close to 10 years of my life. I’m currently 4 months sober from alcohol and I’ve never felt stronger. I’ve taken my power back and I am finally in control.
I know I’m not the only one who has gone through something similar, and I just want to let those affected by SA and substance abuse to know I am here and I stand with you. Thank you to my close friend @yvestruong for helping make my vision come to fruition so beautifully.
